articles.description: Many parts of North, Central and South America lie in the path of an annular solar eclipse that will cross the skies on October 14. Here’s everything you need to know about this exciting event. - Articles from The Weather Channel | weather.com

articles.title: 'Ring of fire' solar eclipse cuts across the Americas, stretching from Oregon to Brazil - KTLA 5
articles.description: A rare “ring of fire” eclipse of the sun cuts across the Americas on Saturday, stretching from Oregon to Brazil, and huge crowds were on the move before dawn...
